net.semanticmetadata.lire.indexers.parallel

Class ParallelIndexer

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.semanticmetadata.lire.indexers.parallel.ParallelIndexer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class ParallelIndexer
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    This class allows for creating indexes in a parallel manner. The class at hand reads files from the disk and acts as producer, while several consumer threads extract the features from the given files.

    Use the methods addExtractor(java.lang.Class<? extends net.semanticmetadata.lire.imageanalysis.features.Extractor>) to add your own features. Check the source of this class -- the main method -- to get an idea.

    Created by mlux on 15/04/2013.

    Author:
    Mathias Lux, mathias@juggle.at, Nektarios Anagnostopoulos, nek.anag@gmail.com

        queueSize - the size of the reading queue to minimize disk usage.

      • setCustomDocumentBuilder

        public void setCustomDocumentBuilder(java.lang.Class<? extends DocumentBuilder> customDocumentBuilder)
        WARNING!! This can be used in order to use a different DocumentBuilder than the GlobalDocumentBuilder, LocalDocumentBuilder or the SimpleDocumentBuilder. Every time only one custom DocumentBuilder can be used. At the same time, using the addExtractor methods one can add other builders to be used at the same time. BUT when using a custom DocumentBuilder, sampling can be used for Local Features. This means that, if you want to use a LocalDocumentBuilder or SimpleDocumentBuilder, you can use them, only combined with pre-computed codebooks!!
        Parameters:
        customDocumentBuilder -
